 ZimClick - Low-Fidelity Wireframes (Task 1)

This repository contains the **Task 1** deliverables for the **CodeAlpha UI/UX Design Internship**. The objective of this project was to architect a clean, conversion-focused mobile user experience funnel for **ZimClick** (Sports & Fitness E-Commerce Store).

 📱 App Architecture & Screens
The wireframe system maps out a standard 4-screen user flow optimized for mobile engagement:

* Home Screen:** Features a left-aligned brand header, prominent search architecture, category filters, and a dual-column featured product grid.
* Shop Grid / Product List:** Designed with high scalable density to smoothly display a large inventory (optimized for 50+ items look).
* Product Details:** Clean typographic hierarchy focusing on product specs, variant selectors (size/color), and a bold primary CTA button.
* Cart & Checkout:** Optimized transaction state with itemized order summaries, item counters, and an intuitive checkout funnel.

 🎨 UI/UX Design Standards Applied
* **Grayscale System:** Built entirely using low-fidelity standards (Black, White, and Gray scales) to prioritize layout structure over visual assets.
* **Content Placeholders:** Utilized standard layout blocks and crossed image placeholders to structure spatial distribution.
* **Grid Consistency:** Maintained a strict structural grid padding across all interface layouts for device-level consistency.

